netSnmpExtendMIB.name: netSnmpExtendMIB

revisions.description: Fixed inconsistencies in the definition of nsExtendConfigTable.

netSnmpExtendMIB.contactinfo: postal: Wes Hardaker P.O. Box 382 Davis CA 95617 email: net-snmp-coders@lists.sourceforge.net
netSnmpExtendMIB.description: Defines a framework for scripted extensions for the Net-SNMP agent.

nsExtendNumEntries.name: nsExtendNumEntries
nsExtendNumEntries.description: The number of rows in the nsExtendConfigTable

nsExtendConfigTable.name: nsExtendConfigTable
nsExtendConfigTable.description: A table of scripted extensions - configuration and (basic) output.

nsExtendConfigEntry.name: nsExtendConfigEntry
nsExtendConfigEntry.description: A conceptual row within the extension table.

nsExtendToken.name: nsExtendToken
nsExtendToken.description: An arbitrary token to identify this extension entry

nsExtendCommand.name: nsExtendCommand
nsExtendCommand.description: The full path of the command binary (or script) to run

nsExtendArgs.name: nsExtendArgs
nsExtendArgs.description: Any command-line arguments for the command

nsExtendInput.name: nsExtendInput
nsExtendInput.description: The standard input for the command

nsExtendCacheTime.name: nsExtendCacheTime
nsExtendCacheTime.description: The length of time for which the output of this command will be cached. During this time, retrieving the output-related values will not reinvoke the command. A value of -1 indicates that the output results should not be cached at all, and retrieving each individual output-related value will invoke the command afresh.

nsExtendExecType.name: nsExtendExecType
nsExtendExecType.description: The mechanism used to invoke the command.

nsExtendRunType.name: nsExtendRunType
nsExtendRunType.description: Used to implement 'push-button' command invocation. The command for a 'run-on-read' entry will be invoked whenever one of the corresponding output-related instances is requested (and assuming the cached value is not still current). The command for a 'run-on-set' entry will only be invoked on receipt of a SET assignment for this object with the value 'run-command'. Reading an instance of this object will always return either 'run-on-read' or 'run-on-set'.

nsExtendStorage.name: nsExtendStorage
nsExtendStorage.description: The storage type for this conceptual row.

nsExtendStatus.name: nsExtendStatus
nsExtendStatus.description: Used to create new rows in the table, in the standard manner. Note that is valid for an instance to be left with the value notInService(2) indefinitely - i.e. the meaning of 'abnormally long' (see RFC 2579, RowStatus) for this table is infinite.

nsExtendOutput1Table.name: nsExtendOutput1Table
nsExtendOutput1Table.description: A table of scripted extensions - configuration and (basic) output.

nsExtendOutput1Entry.name: nsExtendOutput1Entry
nsExtendOutput1Entry.description: A conceptual row within the extension table.

nsExtendOutput1Line.name: nsExtendOutput1Line
nsExtendOutput1Line.description: The first line of output from the command

nsExtendOutputFull.name: nsExtendOutputFull
nsExtendOutputFull.description: The full output from the command, as a single string

nsExtendOutNumLines.name: nsExtendOutNumLines
nsExtendOutNumLines.description: The number of lines of output (and hence the number of rows in nsExtendOutputTable relating to this particular entry).

nsExtendResult.name: nsExtendResult
nsExtendResult.description: The return value of the command.

nsExtendOutput2Table.name: nsExtendOutput2Table
nsExtendOutput2Table.description: A table of (line-based) output from scripted extensions.

nsExtendOutput2Entry.name: nsExtendOutput2Entry
nsExtendOutput2Entry.description: A conceptual row within the line-based output table.

nsExtendLineIndex.name: nsExtendLineIndex
nsExtendLineIndex.description: The index of this line of output. For a given nsExtendToken, this will run from 1 to the corresponding value of nsExtendNumLines.

nsExtendOutLine.name: nsExtendOutLine
nsExtendOutLine.description: A single line of output from the extension command.

nsExtendConfigGroup.name: nsExtendConfigGroup
nsExtendConfigGroup.description: Objects relating to the configuration of extension commands.

nsExtendOutputGroup.name: nsExtendOutputGroup
nsExtendOutputGroup.description: Objects relating to the output of extension commands.
